WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.841 --> 00:00:09.434
- Ezra. stop. Listen.

2
00:00:09.543 --> 00:00:11.603
I'm not gonna hurt you.
Don't run away like that.

3
00:00:12.779 --> 00:00:13.779
Ezra!

4
00:00:14.615 --> 00:00:16.550
A knife doesn't scare
me. young man. Hold still.

5
00:00:18.051 --> 00:00:20.543
Shh!

6
00:00:20.687 --> 00:00:23.748
- Ain't nothin' wrong with that
boy a good whuppin' won't fix.

7
00:00:23.891 --> 00:00:27.453
- Yeah. Think we'll
start with a haircut first.

8
00:00:30.697 --> 00:00:31.960
Let's get to it.

9
00:00:33.967 --> 00:00:36.527
- A woman like that good
with scissors and a Bible?

10
00:00:36.670 --> 00:00:38.332
You ought to marry
her up. Mr. Bohannon.

11
00:00:38.472 --> 00:00:40.498
before Miss Ruth find
her some other lowlife

12
00:00:40.641 --> 00:00:43.338
fancy belt-wearing
huckster that come along.

13
00:00:43.477 --> 00:00:45.957
- You callin' me a fancy lowlife
belt-wearing huckster. Psalms?

14
00:00:50.050 --> 00:00:51.985
- Uh. no sir. Mr. Bohannon.

15
00:00:52.386 --> 00:00:53.997
- All anybody needs to
be concerned with today

16
00:00:54.021 --> 00:00:56.013
is making Cheyenne by tomorrow.

17
00:00:56.423 --> 00:00:58.085
- Yes. sir. Mr. Bohannon.

18
00:01:01.995 --> 00:01:03.987
- All right. y'all. listen up!

19
00:01:04.698 --> 00:01:07.600
That there dot on the
horizon is Cheyenne!

20
00:01:08.835 --> 00:01:11.270
I promised General
Grant hisself...

21
00:01:11.738 --> 00:01:14.936
that we'd make it there
by tomorrow at sunset.

22
00:01:15.075 --> 00:01:17.704
It gives us two days
to lay 5 mile of track.

23
00:01:17.878 --> 00:01:20.279
- Mr. Bohannon.
speaking for the Irish.

24
00:01:20.414 --> 00:01:22.212
all due respect. sir.
but tomorrow's Sunday.

25
00:01:22.349 --> 00:01:23.942
It's the Lord's day.
not a work day.

26
00:01:24.084 --> 00:01:25.484
- Yeah. Yeah.
- That's right.

27
00:01:25.619 --> 00:01:28.214
- Even the Lord makes
exceptions. Mr. Quinn.

28
00:01:29.056 --> 00:01:30.456
And sacrifices.

29
00:01:30.624 --> 00:01:32.320
In fact. the only
thing he don't make

30
00:01:32.459 --> 00:01:34.519
is the extra money I'm
gonna put in your pockets

31
00:01:34.661 --> 00:01:36.861
you get us to Cheyenne on schedule.
- Yeah. that's true.

32
00:01:36.897 --> 00:01:38.229
- This right here...

33
00:01:39.766 --> 00:01:41.257
is the rest of my stock.

34
00:01:42.069 --> 00:01:43.435
I'm cashing it in.

35
00:01:43.570 --> 00:01:45.090
Spreading it around.
Who wants a piece?

36
00:01:45.138 --> 00:01:46.766
- Yeah.
- I want a piece.

37
00:01:46.907 --> 00:01:49.342
- Well. I suppose it's no
sin to work on the Lord's day.

38
00:01:49.476 --> 00:01:52.537
Long as we don't make a habit of it.
- And my crew will take a piece of that.

39
00:01:52.646 --> 00:01:54.205
- Work be our ticket to heaven.

40
00:01:54.314 --> 00:01:55.942
We'll ride this
train and that stock

41
00:01:56.083 --> 00:01:57.449
all the way to Cheyenne.

42
00:02:01.121 --> 00:02:02.953
- We've been
through hell and back.

43
00:02:03.090 --> 00:02:05.753
Indians. rain. drought...

44
00:02:05.892 --> 00:02:07.258
cholera.

45
00:02:09.563 --> 00:02:11.293
You men have
done a hell of a job.

46
00:02:12.332 --> 00:02:13.732
I'm proud of all of y'all.

47
00:02:19.673 --> 00:02:21.164
Now...

48
00:02:21.942 --> 00:02:24.070
you get us to Cheyenne
by tomorrow night.

49
00:02:24.177 --> 00:02:25.645
first two rounds is on me!

50
00:02:25.779 --> 00:02:26.838
Yeah.

51
00:02:26.980 --> 00:02:28.448
- Whores are on Dutch.

52
00:02:28.615 --> 00:02:30.811
- Yeah!
- Get to work!

53
00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:38.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

54
00:03:14.394 --> 00:03:16.829
- Good God. he's going to do it.

55
00:03:16.963 --> 00:03:19.398
- Who is?
- Bohannon!

56
00:03:19.566 --> 00:03:21.364
He's right there.

57
00:03:21.501 --> 00:03:25.029
Tomorrow. he'll be right
here. laying tracks in my town.

58
00:03:26.373 --> 00:03:28.001
Pennies on my eyes.

59
00:03:28.141 --> 00:03:29.234
- Our town.

60
00:03:30.510 --> 00:03:33.173
You keep leaving that
rather important part out.

61
00:03:35.882 --> 00:03:39.375
Hmm. How did you sleep
last night. Mr. Durant?

62
00:03:40.554 --> 00:03:43.353
Those goose-down
mattresses. they cost a fortune.

63
00:03:47.094 --> 00:03:48.187
What?

64
00:03:49.896 --> 00:03:52.161
- You sell cattle to Bohannon.

65
00:03:52.265 --> 00:03:54.860
lend me money to build <i>our</i> town.

66
00:03:55.001 --> 00:03:57.368
You build a hotel on
the best lot in Cheyenne

67
00:03:57.504 --> 00:04:00.872
and charge me full
fare to rent a room.

68
00:04:01.007 --> 00:04:03.340
Now. if I didn't know better.

69
00:04:04.211 --> 00:04:08.046
I might think you were playing both
ends against the middle. Mrs. Palmer.

70
00:04:08.181 --> 00:04:09.240
- Hmm!

71
00:04:10.550 --> 00:04:12.041
Thank you. Abigail.

72
00:04:14.588 --> 00:04:17.114
Often. your interests
align with mine.

73
00:04:17.290 --> 00:04:18.690
Occasionally. they don't.

74
00:04:18.792 --> 00:04:23.093
Your interests align with mine?

75
00:04:23.230 --> 00:04:25.028
I think you got it backwards.

76
00:04:28.068 --> 00:04:29.434
Mmm.

77
00:04:29.569 --> 00:04:33.062
Mmm! Quail?

78
00:04:33.206 --> 00:04:34.435
- Dove.

79
00:04:36.409 --> 00:04:38.401
The French call it detente.

80
00:04:39.045 --> 00:04:41.879
It's what you and Bohannon better
reach before he reaches Cheyenne.

81
00:04:41.982 --> 00:04:45.111
- Make peace with
Bohannon? To what end?

82
00:04:46.319 --> 00:04:47.753
- You promised me
Cheyenne would be

83
00:04:47.888 --> 00:04:50.119
the most important
railroad city in America.

84
00:04:50.257 --> 00:04:51.697
How are you going
to accomplish that

85
00:04:51.792 --> 00:04:53.988
without the cooperation
of the railroad?

86
00:04:55.729 --> 00:04:58.597
- You are an exasperating
woman. Mrs. Palmer.

87
00:04:58.732 --> 00:05:01.930
- Why? Because I talk
like a blunt-talkin' man?

88
00:05:02.068 --> 00:05:03.661
- Mmm.

89
00:05:03.804 --> 00:05:05.773
- Send Bohannon a telegram.

90
00:05:06.139 --> 00:05:09.075
Invite him to lunch. Today.

91
00:05:09.743 --> 00:05:11.006
Work it out.

92
00:05:13.113 --> 00:05:15.514
- Nothing is that
easy with Bohannon.

93
00:05:15.649 --> 00:05:18.084
- I am not sure
he's the problem.

94
00:05:33.099 --> 00:05:34.123
- That's him.

95
00:05:50.283 --> 00:05:52.115
- Lot of guns down there.

96
00:05:52.853 --> 00:05:56.813
- All the guns in the world will
not protect Cullen Bohannon.

97
00:05:56.957 --> 00:05:58.858
Ya! Ya!

98
00:06:48.041 --> 00:06:49.065
- Ruth.

99
00:06:50.744 --> 00:06:52.337
Ruth.

100
00:06:52.412 --> 00:06:54.472
- Mr. Bohannon.

101
00:06:54.614 --> 00:06:56.344
This just came for you.

102
00:07:00.954 --> 00:07:02.388
- She wrote this down right?

103
00:07:02.956 --> 00:07:04.288
- Yes. sir.

104
00:07:05.425 --> 00:07:06.859
- Thank you. Luke.

105
00:07:10.397 --> 00:07:11.865
Ruth.

106
00:07:19.873 --> 00:07:21.432
Where's Ruth at?

107
00:07:24.477 --> 00:07:27.276
Hey. she gave you a
haircut. Looks good.

108
00:07:39.726 --> 00:07:40.921
Ruth?

109
00:07:44.597 --> 00:07:47.123
- I've kept you out of your bed
long enough. Mr. Bohannon.

110
00:07:47.267 --> 00:07:49.168
I'll be on the noon
train to Omaha.

111
00:07:49.302 --> 00:07:50.827
There's an orphanage
in Council Bluffs.

112
00:07:50.971 --> 00:07:52.963
I can take Ezra...
- Ruth...

113
00:07:56.676 --> 00:07:58.406
Stop it.

114
00:08:09.155 --> 00:08:12.683
- I'm sorry. but if a tenant of
Christ's teachings is selflessness.

115
00:08:12.826 --> 00:08:15.625
then I have been
a poor disciple.

116
00:08:17.030 --> 00:08:19.363
- Sean McGinnis
was a troubled soul.

117
00:08:19.499 --> 00:08:22.899
His brother relieved him of his troubles.
Now. that weren't through no fault of yours.

118
00:08:23.470 --> 00:08:25.837
- Sean came to me
to unburden himself.

119
00:08:25.972 --> 00:08:28.032
He came seeking solace.

120
00:08:28.174 --> 00:08:29.267
And...

121
00:08:32.779 --> 00:08:34.645
and I denied him.

122
00:08:42.689 --> 00:08:44.055
Perhaps I would do well

123
00:08:44.190 --> 00:08:46.625
to spend some time
away from this place.

124
00:08:58.505 --> 00:09:00.201
- The men need you here. Ruth.

125
00:09:05.311 --> 00:09:08.645
- I have made no
difference in their lives.

126
00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:13.083
- Well. you've given me comfort.

127
00:09:13.219 --> 00:09:16.656
And you've given me hell too.

128
00:09:16.756 --> 00:09:19.248
In equal parts. according
to what I deserve.

129
00:09:19.392 --> 00:09:21.258
And I ain't the only one.

130
00:09:24.697 --> 00:09:27.531
- Do you want me to
stay. Mr. Bohannon?

131
00:09:33.907 --> 00:09:38.242
- Hell on wheels just needs
a good preacher. Ruth.

132
00:09:38.711 --> 00:09:41.875
And you are. You
are a good preacher.

133
00:09:45.919 --> 00:09:49.219
Tomorrow's Sunday. The
men expect to get preached to.

134
00:09:50.757 --> 00:09:53.591
They expect you to do the
preaching. That's all there is to it.

135
00:09:56.563 --> 00:09:58.293
Come on. boy. Get your hat.

136
00:09:58.431 --> 00:10:00.093
We're going to Cheyenne.

137
00:10:06.473 --> 00:10:07.736
You have a seat.

138
00:10:08.575 --> 00:10:10.134
You stay right there. too.

139
00:10:11.111 --> 00:10:13.046
Mickey.
- You're just in time.

140
00:10:13.813 --> 00:10:17.079
Chief of police over there
is full as a gypsy's bra.

141
00:10:17.217 --> 00:10:19.482
and I'm almost
positive that Wallace

142
00:10:19.652 --> 00:10:21.382
is dealing off the
bottom of the deck.

143
00:10:23.623 --> 00:10:25.251
- Thank you.

144
00:10:27.727 --> 00:10:29.286
- Take two.

145
00:10:41.975 --> 00:10:44.103
- Take your damn scalp
and get the hell out of here.

146
00:10:48.781 --> 00:10:51.307
Oh. you can leave that.
- That's my money.

147
00:10:51.451 --> 00:10:52.749
- Not anymore. it ain't.

148
00:10:54.087 --> 00:10:55.453
- Um...

149
00:11:06.332 --> 00:11:08.927
- You best give me
that. It cost me $1.

150
00:11:10.637 --> 00:11:13.539
- Agh! Thanks for the warning.

151
00:11:14.707 --> 00:11:16.005
Ugh!

152
00:11:18.211 --> 00:11:19.839
You know what that is?

153
00:11:22.182 --> 00:11:23.707
That's a telegram.

154
00:11:24.717 --> 00:11:27.881
From Durant. Asking
me to come to Cheyenne.

155
00:11:29.822 --> 00:11:30.846
- What for?

156
00:11:31.791 --> 00:11:33.769
- If I didn't know better.
I'd say he's surrendering.

157
00:11:33.793 --> 00:11:36.633
He knows we're gonna be in Cheyenne
tomorrow and wants to broker a deal.

158
00:11:36.663 --> 00:11:37.995
Know what that means?

159
00:11:38.865 --> 00:11:40.629
Hey.

160
00:11:42.969 --> 00:11:44.904
We won the damn war. damn it.

161
00:11:48.208 --> 00:11:50.905
- Ain't none of us out
here never won nothin'.

162
00:11:51.477 --> 00:11:53.036
And never will.

163
00:11:54.714 --> 00:11:56.910
Otherwise. we wouldn't
be here in the first place.

164
00:12:00.053 --> 00:12:01.316
Mmm.

165
00:12:03.022 --> 00:12:04.581
- Quit your damn bitchin'.

166
00:12:05.558 --> 00:12:07.083
You're comin' to
Cheyenne. Let's go.

167
00:12:07.227 --> 00:12:08.820
- Well. what you need me for?

168
00:12:09.562 --> 00:12:12.396
- Victory needs an
audience. and you is he.

169
00:12:12.532 --> 00:12:13.693
Come on. my friend.

170
00:12:45.231 --> 00:12:46.631
- Where my money at?

171
00:12:46.699 --> 00:12:48.964
- Put your hat on.
You might find it.

172
00:12:49.636 --> 00:12:51.434
Uh-uh. Come on.

173
00:13:06.753 --> 00:13:08.415
- I was wondering
when you'd come.

174
00:13:08.554 --> 00:13:11.820
- Forgive me. If you're
praying. I can come back.

175
00:13:14.661 --> 00:13:16.152
- How will you tell it?

176
00:13:18.097 --> 00:13:20.123
"Cain and Abel"?

177
00:13:22.101 --> 00:13:25.594
"Fallen woman pastor brings
murder into her church"?

178
00:13:28.508 --> 00:13:30.773
- Is that how you
see yourself...

179
00:13:31.177 --> 00:13:33.305
a fallen woman pastor?

180
00:13:42.322 --> 00:13:45.349
This doesn't have to
be about the newspaper.

181
00:13:57.637 --> 00:14:00.971
- Do you ever wonder how we
came to be in this forsaken place?

182
00:14:04.510 --> 00:14:05.773
- Well...

183
00:14:07.380 --> 00:14:10.214
if I believed in God.

184
00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:13.149
which... I don't...

185
00:14:14.287 --> 00:14:16.313
I would say it's for my sins.

186
00:14:18.825 --> 00:14:21.954
- I have just enough
faith to condemn me

187
00:14:22.061 --> 00:14:24.462
for the sins I've committed
since I arrived here.

188
00:14:27.200 --> 00:14:28.463
- What sins?

189
00:14:34.207 --> 00:14:36.369
- I've been praying
for understanding.

190
00:14:37.076 --> 00:14:39.341
- It-it isn't...

191
00:14:39.479 --> 00:14:42.677
a sin to pray for
understanding. is it?

192
00:14:42.815 --> 00:14:45.182
- Oh. we can't know God's will.

193
00:14:48.588 --> 00:14:50.386
- So...

194
00:14:51.357 --> 00:14:55.089
where does that leave
you? Will you... go back east?

195
00:15:00.199 --> 00:15:01.997
- Mr. Bohannon has...

196
00:15:02.602 --> 00:15:04.935
asked me to stay
with the railroad.

197
00:15:05.538 --> 00:15:09.600
- So... perhaps he's the
answer to your prayers.

198
00:15:13.946 --> 00:15:16.211
- A man with the mark of Cain.

199
00:15:19.886 --> 00:15:21.548
That would be ironic.

200
00:15:29.462 --> 00:15:31.761
- You have feelings for him.

201
00:15:31.898 --> 00:15:33.264
Don't you?

202
00:15:45.912 --> 00:15:47.744
- Why we going to Cheyenne?

203
00:15:50.550 --> 00:15:53.247
- I already told you.
- No. you ain't.

204
00:15:53.386 --> 00:15:55.787
When you tell me?
- Would you just shut...

205
00:15:55.922 --> 00:15:58.892
Shut up. You're
makin' my head hurt.

206
00:16:04.831 --> 00:16:06.663
Ho.

207
00:16:10.903 --> 00:16:12.166
- What we doing?

208
00:16:12.939 --> 00:16:14.619
- Men coming up behind
us. Don't look back.

209
00:16:18.578 --> 00:16:19.876
- Who they?

210
00:16:20.012 --> 00:16:22.277
- Told you not to look back.
- Who is it?

211
00:16:23.749 --> 00:16:24.773
- Damn it. Elam!

212
00:16:26.152 --> 00:16:28.280
Come on. Get up.

213
00:16:28.421 --> 00:16:29.946
Get back on.

214
00:16:34.594 --> 00:16:37.359
Get the boy to Cheyenne.
fast and straight. Hyah!

215
00:16:49.175 --> 00:16:51.838
Aah!

216
00:16:51.978 --> 00:16:53.674
Hyah!

217
00:17:12.865 --> 00:17:14.891
Get that chair!

218
00:17:15.868 --> 00:17:17.632
Come on!

219
00:17:20.540 --> 00:17:21.872
Don't move.

220
00:17:22.008 --> 00:17:25.240
- Bohannon! What in
God's name is going on?

221
00:17:25.378 --> 00:17:27.404
- I'd keep my head down if I was you!
- Ooh!

222
00:17:28.481 --> 00:17:30.746
- Go!
- Ugh!

223
00:17:31.817 --> 00:17:32.841
- Hyah! Hyah!
- Hyah!

224
00:17:42.728 --> 00:17:44.253
- Who the hell's out there?
- No idea.

225
00:17:48.034 --> 00:17:50.196
- Go. go. go!
- What's that smell?

226
00:17:50.336 --> 00:17:52.567
- I'm drunk.
- Christ!

227
00:17:52.705 --> 00:17:54.139
- Yep.

228
00:17:54.273 --> 00:17:56.401
Get that boy upstairs!
- You get him upstairs.

229
00:17:56.542 --> 00:17:58.909
This is my hotel. and those
windows cost a fortune!

230
00:17:59.045 --> 00:18:00.445
Otis! Where's my yellow boy?

231
00:18:05.785 --> 00:18:07.686
- You a good shot?
- I can take the ear

232
00:18:07.820 --> 00:18:09.789
off a rabbit at 200
yards. left or right.

233
00:18:09.922 --> 00:18:11.891
- Otis. you got any coffee?
- In the back.

234
00:18:12.024 --> 00:18:13.390
- Bring it! Here.

235
00:18:16.596 --> 00:18:18.963
Anybody comes through that
door or that door. you shoot 'em.

236
00:18:19.098 --> 00:18:20.930
Come on. You know
how to use that thing?

237
00:18:21.968 --> 00:18:23.459
All right. then.

238
00:18:33.746 --> 00:18:34.941
Stay right there.

239
00:18:48.961 --> 00:18:50.657
Shit!

240
00:18:50.796 --> 00:18:52.765
No matter what happens.

241
00:18:52.898 --> 00:18:54.457
no matter what you hear.

242
00:18:54.634 --> 00:18:56.626
you don't leave till I
come back. you got me?

243
00:18:56.769 --> 00:18:59.000
All right.

244
00:19:01.774 --> 00:19:03.003
I ain't leavin' you. son.

245
00:19:09.749 --> 00:19:11.115
Now. you drink that.

246
00:19:11.250 --> 00:19:13.412
Them men come at
us on the way over here.

247
00:19:13.519 --> 00:19:14.817
After your invite.

248
00:19:14.954 --> 00:19:17.446
- Not everything bad
that happens to you

249
00:19:17.590 --> 00:19:19.001
is my fault. Bohannon.
- Mostly it is.

250
00:19:19.025 --> 00:19:20.789
- I told you there was
a range war coming.

251
00:19:20.926 --> 00:19:23.020
Not all my neighbors are
happy with my decision

252
00:19:23.162 --> 00:19:24.824
to sell livestock
to the railroad.

253
00:19:25.498 --> 00:19:27.763
Or build this town.
- No. they come after me.

254
00:19:27.867 --> 00:19:30.336
- I don't think this is a
first for you. Bohannon.

255
00:19:31.003 --> 00:19:32.528
- Whoever they is.

256
00:19:32.672 --> 00:19:34.664
they got us outnumbered
and outgunned.

257
00:19:35.474 --> 00:19:37.466
We gonna need a plan.

258
00:19:37.610 --> 00:19:40.671
- Otis. you got any food. water?
- Not much.

259
00:19:41.113 --> 00:19:42.113
- Shit.

260
00:19:42.181 --> 00:19:45.310
We got women and children in
here. All they got to do is wait us out.

261
00:19:46.686 --> 00:19:48.746
- This town got a
telegraph office. don't it?

262
00:19:48.888 --> 00:19:51.153
- Yes. Up the street.

263
00:19:51.290 --> 00:19:53.691
- Major Bendix only
a few hours from here.

264
00:19:53.826 --> 00:19:56.591
- You go out there. you'll be dead
long before the cavalry gets here.

265
00:19:56.729 --> 00:19:58.994
- That is a
distinct possibility.

266
00:20:03.536 --> 00:20:06.506
You keep 'em off me till I get
across the street. we might make it.

267
00:20:07.673 --> 00:20:10.973
- You got that
boy upstairs. I'll go.

268
00:20:11.143 --> 00:20:12.304
- What?

269
00:20:12.411 --> 00:20:14.073
- You want me to cover you?

270
00:20:16.749 --> 00:20:19.048
Drunk or sober. you
a better shot than me.

271
00:20:23.022 --> 00:20:24.718
Gotta be me that go.

272
00:20:56.889 --> 00:20:58.118
- Bohannon!

273
00:21:02.428 --> 00:21:03.589
You're surrounded!

274
00:21:05.030 --> 00:21:07.590
Come out! Guns down!

275
00:21:08.701 --> 00:21:11.603
You have my word.
nobody'll be hurt.

276
00:21:12.371 --> 00:21:15.034
All we want is Bohannon!

277
00:21:21.413 --> 00:21:22.813
- You ain't believin' him.

278
00:21:22.948 --> 00:21:25.179
- Ain't no sense in
all of us getting killed.

279
00:21:25.317 --> 00:21:26.410
- You're right.

280
00:21:27.153 --> 00:21:29.418
I'll go talk to them. see
what they want with you.

281
00:21:29.555 --> 00:21:31.421
negotiate a settlement.

282
00:21:31.824 --> 00:21:33.258
- Oh!

283
00:21:36.762 --> 00:21:37.821
- What now?

284
00:21:38.798 --> 00:21:41.461
- Otis. how much
whiskey you got?

285
00:21:51.243 --> 00:21:52.267
- Ah!

286
00:22:25.010 --> 00:22:26.171
- Aah!

287
00:22:29.615 --> 00:22:31.174
Aah!

288
00:22:38.357 --> 00:22:39.381
- Damn it.

289
00:22:56.475 --> 00:22:58.205
Aah!

290
00:23:06.752 --> 00:23:07.879
- We too late.

291
00:23:26.405 --> 00:23:27.532
- Oww.

292
00:23:27.673 --> 00:23:29.266
Tell you what.

293
00:23:29.408 --> 00:23:31.604
This railroad business
is funner than shit.

294
00:23:34.713 --> 00:23:38.206
- It beat picking cotton
from can see to can't see.

295
00:23:38.350 --> 00:23:41.047
- First year of the
war I thought...

296
00:23:41.687 --> 00:23:43.383
"Best damn thing that
ever happened to me."

297
00:23:44.924 --> 00:23:46.392
I hated farming.

298
00:23:46.525 --> 00:23:50.621
Rather be anywhere than
ass-deep in Mississippi mud...

299
00:23:50.763 --> 00:23:52.789
running behind a mule all day.

300
00:23:52.932 --> 00:23:55.231
- How long before you
changed your mind?

301
00:23:55.467 --> 00:23:58.062
Just did.

302
00:24:02.474 --> 00:24:04.409
- That little boy
waiting for you.

303
00:24:06.111 --> 00:24:08.080
No matter what happen out there.

304
00:24:08.213 --> 00:24:10.045
you make it to that
hotel. you hear?

305
00:24:10.149 --> 00:24:12.084
- I don't...

306
00:24:12.217 --> 00:24:13.446
you finish that road.

307
00:24:19.425 --> 00:24:20.791
And Elam...

308
00:24:25.898 --> 00:24:27.457
I never freed my slaves.

309
00:24:30.436 --> 00:24:33.099
- I always figured you
was lying about that.

310
00:24:35.507 --> 00:24:37.806
- Ready?
- Mm-hmm.

311
00:24:50.990 --> 00:24:52.424
- Elam.

312
00:24:54.126 --> 00:24:55.424
- I know.

313
00:25:17.683 --> 00:25:18.810
- Ah!

314
00:25:44.243 --> 00:25:45.541
- Psst.

315
00:26:22.614 --> 00:26:24.606
- Ah!
- Ah! They stormed the place.

316
00:26:24.750 --> 00:26:26.048
- Where the boy at?

317
00:26:26.185 --> 00:26:28.416
- Wha... they took him.

318
00:26:30.722 --> 00:26:32.384
- They took that
boy to get at you.

319
00:26:34.893 --> 00:26:36.259
- You might need this.

320
00:26:44.103 --> 00:26:45.935
- I'm gonna take the back.

321
00:27:17.803 --> 00:27:19.271
Aah!

322
00:27:28.180 --> 00:27:29.273
- Aah!

323
00:27:52.704 --> 00:27:54.104
- Let the boy go.

324
00:27:54.873 --> 00:27:56.774
- Soon as you
drop your gun belt.

325
00:28:02.114 --> 00:28:03.980
- Boy ain't got
nothin' to do with this.

326
00:28:08.520 --> 00:28:09.544
What you want?

327
00:28:09.721 --> 00:28:12.020
- You for the boy.

328
00:28:14.159 --> 00:28:16.719
- All right. Let him go.

329
00:28:17.129 --> 00:28:20.190
- You drop your gun belt and
you come out where I can see you.

330
00:28:51.396 --> 00:28:53.126
- Mr. Ferguson's
back along the way.

331
00:28:53.265 --> 00:28:55.427
You go with him back
to the hotel. Go on.

332
00:28:55.567 --> 00:28:56.660
Ezra.

333
00:28:58.103 --> 00:29:00.197
You listen to Miss
Ruth. you hear me?

334
00:29:02.040 --> 00:29:03.201
Go on.

335
00:29:35.274 --> 00:29:36.833
- They say why they took him?

336
00:29:36.975 --> 00:29:39.087
- I think it's the Mormons
for him taking the workers.

337
00:29:39.111 --> 00:29:40.977
- Huntington warned
him about that.

338
00:29:41.113 --> 00:29:43.412
I know you're not fool
enough to go after him.

339
00:29:44.249 --> 00:29:45.808
- I'm gonna do what
needs to be done.

340
00:29:45.951 --> 00:29:49.581
Bohannon said keep building
the railroad with or without him.

341
00:29:50.255 --> 00:29:51.815
I aim it to be with him.
- Mr. Ferguson.

342
00:29:51.957 --> 00:29:53.425
Mr. Ferguson!

343
00:29:54.726 --> 00:29:57.252
Going after him is suicide.

344
00:29:57.396 --> 00:29:58.762
Look around you.

345
00:29:58.897 --> 00:30:01.799
Do you want to face
those men again. alone?

346
00:30:01.933 --> 00:30:03.765
- I'm gonna keep my
word to Bohannon.

347
00:30:04.303 --> 00:30:07.273
Then I'm busting him
free. You can count on that.

348
00:30:31.430 --> 00:30:33.695
- Uh. Miss Ellison.
- Yes?

349
00:30:34.533 --> 00:30:35.865
- Uh...

350
00:30:36.001 --> 00:30:38.197
Mrs. Toole will be
leaving us. I'm afraid.

351
00:30:38.337 --> 00:30:39.771
- What do you mean?

352
00:30:39.871 --> 00:30:42.306
- Well. the woman's
a whore. Miss Ellison.

353
00:30:45.110 --> 00:30:46.703
- Mrs. Toole is not a whore.

354
00:30:47.312 --> 00:30:49.757
And even if she were. I expect
that to be as little concern to you

355
00:30:49.781 --> 00:30:51.977
as your previous
misadventures are to me.

356
00:30:53.051 --> 00:30:54.542
- I run a respectable
establishment.

357
00:30:56.688 --> 00:30:58.987
- Prior to becoming
Mr. Mortimer Ramsey.

358
00:30:59.124 --> 00:31:01.992
proprietor of this hotel.
you lived in Omaha?

359
00:31:02.561 --> 00:31:06.396
Calling yourself... ah.
Dr. Henry Whitford...

360
00:31:06.631 --> 00:31:08.463
until the deaths
of three patients

361
00:31:08.567 --> 00:31:10.661
hastened a name
change and a move west.

362
00:31:12.003 --> 00:31:13.494
- Clearly. you are mistaken.

363
00:31:13.638 --> 00:31:16.904
- The deaths were attributed to an
overdose of "perpetual sunshine"...

364
00:31:17.042 --> 00:31:20.444
a miracle elixir you widely prescribed.
claiming it would cure just about anything.

365
00:31:20.579 --> 00:31:24.539
which I guess. technically.
death does. doesn't it?

366
00:31:26.685 --> 00:31:28.278
I'm a newspaper
woman. Mr. Ramsey.

367
00:31:28.420 --> 00:31:30.582
People talk to me about
this. that. and the other.

368
00:31:30.722 --> 00:31:33.317
Now. as for my guest.

369
00:31:34.092 --> 00:31:35.492
she will be staying on

370
00:31:35.594 --> 00:31:38.086
until she finds other.
more suitable. lodgings.

371
00:31:38.230 --> 00:31:39.698
Are we clear on that?

372
00:31:40.265 --> 00:31:41.858
- Yes.

373
00:31:42.868 --> 00:31:44.734
- Lovely. Have a good day.

374
00:31:52.711 --> 00:31:54.543
- I don't want to
cause no trouble.

375
00:31:54.679 --> 00:31:56.580
- No trouble at all. Eva.

376
00:31:57.449 --> 00:32:00.248
Listen. and if that man
gives you any more guff.

377
00:32:00.385 --> 00:32:03.253
you just talk to me.
okay? Let me know.

378
00:32:15.434 --> 00:32:16.993
- Why you doing this for me?

379
00:32:17.135 --> 00:32:19.468
- You're a good woman. Eva.

380
00:32:19.604 --> 00:32:22.938
You've just had...
some tough luck.

381
00:32:38.256 --> 00:32:39.622
- Thank you.

382
00:32:57.609 --> 00:32:59.271
Uh...

383
00:33:01.012 --> 00:33:02.913
- It's what you want. ain't it?

384
00:33:06.084 --> 00:33:07.677
- Is that what you think?

385
00:33:10.922 --> 00:33:13.153
- Well. I seen the
way you look at me.

386
00:33:16.027 --> 00:33:17.495
- Eva...

387
00:33:21.666 --> 00:33:24.363
that's not why I
asked you to stay here.

388
00:33:26.838 --> 00:33:28.306
- Well. I thought...

389
00:33:30.342 --> 00:33:31.503
- What?

390
00:33:33.044 --> 00:33:35.809
That... that you're not
worthy of my friendship?

391
00:33:38.550 --> 00:33:40.143
Eva. you are.

392
00:33:48.126 --> 00:33:50.288
- I don't accept
no charity. so...

393
00:33:52.397 --> 00:33:54.491
- Eva... stay.

394
00:33:55.066 --> 00:33:57.126
Please.

395
00:34:57.762 --> 00:34:59.390
- Oh. shit.

396
00:35:00.799 --> 00:35:02.495
- I told you...

397
00:35:02.634 --> 00:35:05.069
you owe me a life for
the one you took from me.

398
00:35:53.585 --> 00:35:55.645
- It was me that killed
my brother. Ruth.

399
00:35:55.987 --> 00:35:58.081
It was him that caused it.

400
00:36:00.659 --> 00:36:03.652
And it will be me that
has to answer for it

401
00:36:03.795 --> 00:36:05.661
when the time comes. not you.

402
00:36:09.167 --> 00:36:11.693
- What did that detective
think Sean had done in Boston?

403
00:36:14.172 --> 00:36:16.164
Strangle someone?

404
00:36:17.208 --> 00:36:18.676
A woman?

405
00:36:21.146 --> 00:36:23.706
You led him to believe Sean
was about to do that to me.

406
00:36:23.848 --> 00:36:26.443
- On my mother's
soul. I thought he was.

407
00:36:33.792 --> 00:36:36.023
- We'll never know. will we?

408
00:36:38.863 --> 00:36:40.161
The truth.

409
00:36:42.634 --> 00:36:44.193
What he was.

410
00:36:46.004 --> 00:36:47.996
- The truth is. I
saved your life.

411
00:36:51.309 --> 00:36:52.902
I have faith.

412
00:36:54.379 --> 00:36:56.075
One day you'll see that.

413
00:37:13.565 --> 00:37:15.329
- Listen up. gentlemen.

414
00:37:17.001 --> 00:37:18.697
Cullen Bohannon's gone.

415
00:37:22.340 --> 00:37:24.434
A gang of riders caught
us up in Cheyenne

416
00:37:24.576 --> 00:37:25.737
and took him.

417
00:37:26.711 --> 00:37:29.681
I don't know where.
or if he'll be back.

418
00:37:30.882 --> 00:37:33.784
I don't even know if he alive.
- Raise a posse. Mr. Ferguson.

419
00:37:33.918 --> 00:37:36.251
We'll find him! Yeah!

420
00:37:36.387 --> 00:37:39.880
- We can't afford to lose no
men to no posse. not today.

421
00:37:40.024 --> 00:37:42.459
- Are you saying we
leave him out there to die?

422
00:37:42.594 --> 00:37:45.063
- We get to Cheyenne first.

423
00:37:45.196 --> 00:37:46.459
Then we look for him.

424
00:37:47.932 --> 00:37:50.902
Bohannon hisself say
this railroad come first.

425
00:37:52.537 --> 00:37:54.768
And ain't not one of us be here

426
00:37:54.906 --> 00:37:59.241
except for him and what
he done and how he done it.

427
00:38:01.579 --> 00:38:03.138
We wouldn't be this far...

428
00:38:03.882 --> 00:38:05.316
if it wasn't for him.

429
00:38:05.450 --> 00:38:07.612
- No doubt about that.
- I know that.

430
00:38:08.987 --> 00:38:11.320
We don't get to Cheyenne
by tomorrow night.

431
00:38:11.456 --> 00:38:13.925
Durant gonna come
back and run this railroad.

432
00:38:13.958 --> 00:38:17.258
Whether Bohannon here or not.

433
00:38:18.963 --> 00:38:21.159
Now. Bohannon
worked me to the bone.

434
00:38:21.900 --> 00:38:23.698
But he worked
hisself right next to me.

435
00:38:23.835 --> 00:38:25.633
- That's right.

436
00:38:25.770 --> 00:38:28.934
- He ain't never give none of
us nothing that we ain't earned.

437
00:38:29.073 --> 00:38:32.339
- That's right!
- And when he did. he stand by it.

438
00:38:36.147 --> 00:38:37.843
Bohannon called me a nigger...

439
00:38:40.852 --> 00:38:43.117
but he ain't never
treat me like one.

440
00:38:48.493 --> 00:38:51.327
Durant a man that cheated. lied.

441
00:38:51.462 --> 00:38:54.455
and stole and disrespected
every last one of us!

442
00:38:56.167 --> 00:38:58.295
Now. we gonna get
this track to Cheyenne.

443
00:38:58.436 --> 00:39:00.530
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

444
00:39:00.672 --> 00:39:02.300
- The way Bohannon do.

445
00:39:04.142 --> 00:39:05.201
One rail at a time!

446
00:39:05.343 --> 00:39:06.743
Yeah!

447
00:39:06.878 --> 00:39:07.878
- One rail at a time!

448
00:39:08.012 --> 00:39:10.504
One rail at a time!

449
00:39:10.548 --> 00:39:11.709
- All right. boys!

450
00:39:11.850 --> 00:39:13.716
Let's get to work!

451
00:39:15.353 --> 00:39:17.379
- Let's lay 'em out!
- Y'all grab them spikes!

452
00:39:17.622 --> 00:39:19.284
- Let's all get ready
to go! Come on!

453
00:39:19.390 --> 00:39:21.222
Lift!

